{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"44b83d07-7e9c-4b03-8091-e94516e7854d","content":"You're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9. Here's the recommended pattern for modern MSTest with constructor-injected `TestContext` plus sync and async initialization:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext (MSTest v3+)\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous initialization here\n    }\n\n    // Async initialization — runs before each test\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // Asynchronous initialization here\n        await SomeAsyncSetup();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Test is running\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(true);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** — use for sync setup and receiving `TestContext` via DI (MSTest 3.x+).\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — use for `async` setup since constructors can't be async.\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** — for one-time async setup shared across all tests in the class (must be `static`).\n\nThis replaces the legacy `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern with proper constructor injection.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"310508db-278e-4fe3-84d3-b1bacbeb39a4","outputTokens":334,"requestId":"E3C3:229C6C:17AEA58:1A96140:6A0528B4"},"id":"506e4a81-a9ab-4c3b-82c5-b147ee0df905","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:43:25.280Z","parentId":"d01882aa-4ba6-4a5b-9940-8995aa92715e"}
